{"title":"Always. Be. Knolling.","link":"https://kottke.org/24/08/always-be-knolling-1","date":1723501751000,"content":"\n        <p>You’ve probably seen instances of <a href=\"http://knolling.org/\">knolling</a> without knowing there was a word for it. Knolling at the Apple Store:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knolling-apple.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knolling-apple.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knolling-apple.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"400\" alt=\"Knolling Apple\" /></p>\n\n<p>Knolling the <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/groups/whats_in_your_bag/\">contents of your bag</a>:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knolling-bag.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knolling-bag.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knolling-bag.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" alt=\"Knolling Bag\" /></p>\n\n<p>Knolling a recipe for <a href=\"http://www.fb.se/work/ikea/homemade-is-best\">a book</a>:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knolling-food.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knolling-food.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knolling-food.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"438\" alt=\"Knolling Food\" /></p>\n\n<p>Knolling the parts of a machine:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knolling-motorcycle.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knolling-motorcycle.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knolling-motorcycle.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"411\" alt=\"Knolling Motorcycle\" /></p>\n\n<p>Knolling is the practice of organizing objects in parallel or at 90° angles. The term has been popularized by artist <a href=\"http://www.tomsachs.org/\">Tom Sachs</a>; he picked it up from <a href=\"http://andrewkromelow.com/\">Andrew Kromelow</a> when both were working at Frank Gehry’s furniture fabrication shop. Gehry was designing chairs for furniture company <a href=\"http://www.knoll.com\">Knoll</a>, and Kromelow would arrange unused tools in a manner similar to Knoll furniture. Hence, knolling.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knoll-sofa.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knoll-sofa.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/knoll-sofa.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"297\" alt=\"Knoll Sofa\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Update:</strong> <a href=\"http://thingsorganizedneatly.tumblr.com/\">Things Organized Neatly</a> is really something. Lots of knolling.</p>\n\n         <p><em>[This is a vintage post originally from Mar 2014.]</em></p>\n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Andrew%20Kromelow\">Andrew Kromelow</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/design\">design</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Knoll\">Knoll</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/language\">language</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/timeless%20posts\">timeless posts</a> · <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Tom%20Sachs\">Tom Sachs</a></p>\n\n        \n\n    ","author":"Jason Kottke","siteTitle":"Kottke","siteHash":"89a883271b4598f9b33ebe87be70d38557bcd266e68aee521a8f93622e0ab723","entryHash":"6de0ad8df5cc66584090e36fed206aee87643c51f41bbf0d8a239deaa9796981","category":"default"}